Steps to Build NodeJS app with Firebase:
========================================
1) Install NodeJS (Comes with NPM)
2) Install package.json file #npm init , #then npm install express -save ; then
   when you pass it on to another developer they can just do #npm install
3) Install Nodemon: https://www.npmjs.com/package/nodemon
   #npm install -g nodemon
   #nodemon app.js
4) Install Express: https://www.npmjs.com/package/express
5) Paste HTML Form with Node.js on github to project
6) Go to Firebase, and create a new project
7) Create Firestore real-time database
8) Download Service account credentials from Firebase console to your project:
   Ex)
   Project Settings > Service Accounts >  Firebase Admin SDK > Node.js > Generate new private key
9) Add the Firebase Admin SDK to our app: 
  #npm install firebase-admin --save

10)
